Note that if all you want to do is check if the current executable has this deadcode elimination problem, there is a simpler way to do it:

```
func TestDeadcodeEliminated(t *testing.T) {
	buf, err := exec.Command("go", "tool", "nm", yourexecutable).CombinedOutput()
	if err != nil {
		t.Fatalf("error executing go tool nm %s: %v", yourexecutable, err)
	}
	if strings.Contains(string(buf), "MethodByName") {
		t.Fatal("output of go tool nm contains MethodByName")
	}
}
```

This is how (delve does it)[https://github.com/go-delve/delve/blob/7f42ac85643834e2d2eae197d34ef501cd5391e8/cmd/dlv/dlv_test.go#L1406]

