Hello!

I used SAST tool Svace and encountered a potential handle leak in `x/net/websocket/hybi.go` in function `hybiClientHandshake`. In particular, in following code:

```go
resp, err := http.ReadResponse(br, &http.Request{Method: "GET"})
if err != nil {
	return err
}
if resp.StatusCode != 101 {
	return ErrBadStatus
}
```

If I understand usage of `Response.Body` correctly, it should be closed after Body was processed and it is the caller's responsibility to close it. But in mentioned code there is a potential scenario when Body wouldn't be closed before execution flow will exit current function (`resp.StatusCode != 101` and after that there is also no closing), which may lead to leak.

So will it make sense to close Body explicitly, f.e.:

```go
resp, err := http.ReadResponse(br, &http.Request{Method: "GET"})
if err != nil {
	return err
}
defer resp.Body.Close()    // < ---
if resp.StatusCode != 101 {
	return ErrBadStatus
}
```

Thank you for your time and expertise!

